  "rawMarkdown" : "---\nsource: https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/security\/secprotocoltype\ncrawled: 2025-12-14T16:42:01Z\n---\n\n# SecProtocolType\n\n**Enumeration**\n\nThe protocol type associated with an Internet password.\n\n## Declaration\n\n```swift\nenum SecProtocolType\n```\n\n## Constants\n\n- **SecProtocolType.FTP**: Indicates FTP.\n- **SecProtocolType.ftpAccount**: Indicates a client side FTP account. The usage of this constant is deprecated as of macOS 10.3.\n- **SecProtocolType.HTTP**: Indicates HTTP.\n- **SecProtocolType.IRC**: Indicates IRC.\n- **SecProtocolType.NNTP**: Indicates NNTP.\n- **SecProtocolType.POP3**: Indicates POP3.\n- **SecProtocolType.SMTP**: Indicates SMTP.\n- **SecProtocolType.SOCKS**: Indicates SOCKS.\n- **SecProtocolType.IMAP**: Indicates IMAP.\n- **SecProtocolType.LDAP**: Indicates LDAP.\n- **SecProtocolType.appleTalk**: Indicates AFP over AppleTalk.\n- **SecProtocolType.AFP**: Indicates AFP over TCP.\n- **SecProtocolType.telnet**: Indicates Telnet.\n- **SecProtocolType.SSH**: Indicates SSH.\n- **SecProtocolType.FTPS**: Indicates FTP over TLS\/SSL.\n- **SecProtocolType.HTTPS**: Indicates HTTP over TLS\/SSL.\n- **SecProtocolType.httpProxy**: Indicates HTTP proxy.\n- **SecProtocolType.httpsProxy**: Indicates HTTPS proxy.\n- **SecProtocolType.ftpProxy**: Indicates FTP proxy.\n- **SecProtocolType.CIFS**: Indicates CIFS.\n- **SecProtocolType.SMB**: Indicates SMB.\n- **SecProtocolType.RTSP**: Indicates RTSP.\n- **SecProtocolType.rtspProxy**: Indicates RTSP proxy.\n- **SecProtocolType.DAAP**: Indicates DAAP.\n- **SecProtocolType.EPPC**: Indicates Remote Apple Events.\n- **SecProtocolType.IPP**: Indicates IPP.\n- **SecProtocolType.NNTPS**: Indicates NNTP over TLS\/SSL.\n- **SecProtocolType.LDAPS**: Indicates LDAP over TLS\/SSL.\n- **SecProtocolType.telnetS**: Indicates Telnet over TLS\/SSL.\n- **SecProtocolType.IMAPS**: Indicates IMAP4 over TLS\/SSL.\n- **SecProtocolType.IRCS**: Indicates IRC over TLS\/SSL.\n- **SecProtocolType.POP3S**: Indicates POP3 over TLS\/SSL.\n- **SecProtocolType.cvSpserver**: Indicates CVS pserver.\n- **SecProtocolType.SVN**: Indicates Subversion.\n- **SecProtocolType.any**: Indicates that any protocol is acceptable.\n\n## Initializers\n\n- **init(rawValue:)**\n\n## Conforms To\n\n- BitwiseCopyable\n- Equatable\n- Hashable\n- RawRepresentable\n- Sendable\n- SendableMetatype\n\n",
